title: Boys soccer: MCS drops to No. 2 in final poll
text:
Boys soccer: MCS drops to No. 2 in final poll Staff report 10:57 p.m. EDT October 21, 2015 STK Stock CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
COLUMBUS - After leading the Division III boys soccer coaches state poll all season, Mansfield Christian fell to No. 2 behind Cincinnati Summit Country Day in the final poll. 
Mansfield Christian is 14-0-2 and the defending Division III state champions. Summit Country Day is 13-3. 
The Ontario girls were sixth in Division II with a 14-2 record, while Clear Fork reappeared in the poll at No. 14. Mapleton is 12th in girls Division III. Read or Share this story: http://ohne.ws/1LNe7S2 MORE STORIES
